title: CAM (2018) Ending Explained and Algorithm Theory!
author: Think Story
comment: I sound like a crazy person in this video, lol. Also, forget to mention one of the dudes in the chat room is named "Mad_Hatter" and she has a cat that looks like some of the renditions of the Cheshire Cat from "Alice in Wonderland."

Here's my theory:
I believe this movie is a modern day rendition of Alice in Wonderland. In this case though, "wonderland" is actually an online life. It shows how one can get so caught up in a life online that you lose touch with what's real life and what's just a fake persona.
She went into a coma after the vibrator machine thing. Her vision went blurry and like didn't wake up until the next day.....explains the Alice in Wonderland thing.
In the beginning, she mentions on the phone that Tinker is an IT guy. I think that's a significant detail. I think he's the one doing the copying. he possibly works for the cam company.

It’s the creators/owns of the site that are stealing the identities.  When Alice called customer service she mentioned they take 50% of what she makes, by having a bot do the show they get 100% ..Tinker guy was friends with all of them just like the creater of Facebook was on FB. Alice also mentioned he was a programmer or something like that during her first FaceTime conversation with him in the beginning of the movie.
